Battleships
-------- 
    Cruisers
        -faster longer range weapons
    Battleships
        -"normal" infantry
    -- Dreadnaughts
        -built quickly by the british, unprecedented sizxe and speed biggest guns, goal of making ecery other battleship"obsolete"
        -10-12 inch main guns and armor
        - once britain maide these gunships everyone wanted to make one.
    Capital ships
        - dreadnaugth mixed with cruisers
        --sacrifices protection for speed

Aliances and arms race
-------------------
    - german law to build dreadnaught and battle cruisers
    - germans and british going back in forth to build a bigger navy and stronger ships.
    - if country wanted to be considered a great country concensis was that you had to have a dreadnaught/ strong navy "kindaa like a pre nuke nuke"
    1,2,3  navy = GB, Germany, Franch/US
    
Nationalism, Social Darwinism, Cult of offensive
---------------------------------------------
    -behind the expensive arms race and alliance making: popular support, or fear (security dilemma--spiral of tension and insecurity)
        -sources of aggresive policies and popular support: new ideas and beliefs that were seen as a natural and "scientific"
    -nationilst agendas 
        -militarism
    -Social darwinism
        -darwinian concepts became very popular "struggle for existance" and "survival of the fittest"
            - everyone believed they were the "fittest"
    -Cult of the offensive
        -succes of the prussian army in the wars of german unification made prussian military doctrine fashionable, and were considered in a Social Darwiniian light
        -"Offense wins wars" was he general idea the core of the beleif that you should attack first and attack hard. (general kreise)
            - new tech and new military tech all prioritise defense
            - trenches, bayonets, artillary

